<br>
The Linksys routers have all sorts of options from on-demand connecting to firewall options, etc.<br>
<br>
Proxying is much better for hosting services, but you would typically need a computer instead of the Linksys to perform such a chore.<br>
<br>
I have both a static IP ADSL connection and a dynamic one.  The static is slightly more reliable, but both work.  The static costs me $15 more a month, but provides 5 public addresses.<br>
<br>
BTW. See that picture on the box. Low center.  Says &quot;Supports PPPoE&quot; ??<br>
